formattedAddress: 73 W 105th St, New York, NY 10025, USA
adrFormatAddress: 73 W 105th St, New York, NY 10025, USA

originalText.text:
I was very disappointed today. 1st: on google, it shows the location being open at 7am but they dont open at 7am. 2nd: I got there at 9am and the owner is standing outside like he is locked out and waiting for someone to come with the key. 3rd: I came back at 9:40 am to get the things on my list. I walked over to the candle section and the owner is with an air blower blowing dust towards the back where im standing, i then asked him if he have Butane lighter refill fluid. He sharply said No. As i continue to pick out the tea light candles i came in for, he still had the Air blower on blowing dust in my direction. 4th: As i get towards the register to pay for the candles… there was Butane Lighter refill fluid behind the counter. I point and asked how much is it, he mumbled the price. I am deaf in one ear and require a hearing aid to hear in the other, so if you mumble or speak low, im not going to hear, i didnt wear my hearing aid. I told him i cant hear, so i asked to see the price. So he repeated the price, then he used his hands to make fake sign language. Then he put up 6 fingers mouthing 6$. I still wanted to see the price on the can. All of that extra attitude could have been avoided by letting me see the price labeled on the can. Which was actually 5.49cents and not 6$. Feeling degraded.. i toss the candles i hoped to purchase on the counter and walked out. I went to another dollar store on Amsterdam that had tea light candles I wanted for cheaper and with a bigger bottle of Butane at half the price.

I’ll conclude that i used to enjoy this dollar store when it was being lead by a nice female. The male owner has a passive aggressive attitude that ill say is gentle nasty. He doesn’t belong in customer service. Might lose customers and have to downsize the store again to make room for another business to rent space, if they keep operating at this pace. .
